## Refactoring Patterns

### ğŸ—ï¸ **Component Extraction Pattern**
```typescript
// Before: Large component
const LargeComponent = () => {
  // 200+ lines of mixed concerns
};

// After: Composed components
const LargeComponent = () => {
  return (
    <Container>
      <Header {...headerProps} />
      <Content {...contentProps} />
      <Actions {...actionProps} />
    </Container>
  );
};
```

### ğŸª **Hook Extraction Pattern**
```typescript
// Before: Mixed state in component
const Component = () => {
  const [data, setData] = useState([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState(null);
  
  // Complex fetch logic...
};

// After: Custom hook
const Component = () => {
  const { data, loading, error, refetch } = useAsyncData(fetchData);
  
  // Simple render logic...
};
```

### ğŸ­ **Service Extraction Pattern**
```typescript
// Before: Logic in component
const Component = () => {
  const processData = (rawData) => {
    // 30+ lines of business logic
  };
};

// After: Service class
const Component = () => {
  const processedData = useMemo(() => 
    DataService.process(rawData), 
    [rawData]
  );
};
```

